[0.000, "o", "    \u001b[38;2;100;230;130m\u001b[1mPD-1 Signaling R-HSA-389948\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2mp=0.0042  q=0.0276  genes: PDCD1\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n    \u001b[38;2;100;230;130m\u001b[1mPyroptosis R-HSA-5620971\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2mp=0.0052  q=0.0276  genes: GZMB\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n    \u001b[38;2;100;230;130m\u001b[1mSignaling By NOTCH2 R-HSA-1980145\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2mp=0.0064  q=0.0276  genes: GZMB\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n    \u001b[38;2;100;230;130m\u001b[1mAdaptive Immune System R-HSA-1280218\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2mp=0.0077  q=0.0276  genes: CD8A, PDCD1\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[25.172, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;2;142;68;207m\u001b[1m  ━━ CLAUDE SYNTHESIS ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    This is a canonical cytotoxic T cell signature with an active checkpoint axis. CD8A marks the CD8+ T cell lineage and drives the MHC Class I binding enrichment — these are MHC-I–restricted effectors, not helpers. GZMB is the terminal effector serine protease delivered via perforin pores, and its appearance under both apoptosis (GO:0006915) and pyroptosis (R-HSA-5620971) reflects its dual mechanism: caspase-3 cleavage in target cells plus gasdermin-mediated lytic death. PDCD1 (PD-1) layered on top tells you these CD8+ effectors are antigen-experienced and have been signaling through their TCR long enough to upregulate the inhibitory receptor — this is the molecular fingerprint of tumor-infiltrating or chronically stimulated CD8s, not naïve cells.\r\n    The convergence of the TCR signaling pathway (CD8A + PDCD1) and PD-1 Signaling (R-HSA-389948) is the key clinical signal. PD-1 engagement by PD-L1 recruits SHP-2, dephosphorylates CD3ζ and ZAP70, and shuts down the same TCR cascade these cells are run"]
[0.000, "o", "ning. You are looking at effectors that are simultaneously armed (GZMB) and braked (PDCD1) — the textbook substrate for anti–PD-1/PD-L1 checkpoint blockade. In a tumor context this predicts response to pembrolizumab/nivolumab; in chronic viral infection it predicts the exhausted phenotype Wherry described.\r\n    The Allograft Rejection enrichment via GZMB is not noise — it's the same biology in a different setting. Granzyme B is the dominant effector in acute cellular rejection, and CD8+GZMB+ infiltrates in transplant biopsies are diagnostic. Combined with the lymphocyte/T cell apoptosis terms driven by PDCD1, the signature also captures the contraction phase of an immune response, where activated T cells delete each other and themselves to resolve inflammation.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    GRUBER is not a HGNC symbol and does not map to any enrichment term in your output — it contributed zero signal and should be flagged as an annotation error or a placeholder before this list goes any further. The NOTCH2 ICD term is a weak, GZMB-only hit and is almost certainly spurious co-annotation rather than real NOTCH biology here; I would drop it from the narrative.\r\n    Experimentally, the next moves are obvious: stain for PD-1/CD8/GZMB by multiplex IF to confirm co-expression at single-cell resolution, run a TCR clonality assay to test whether these are clonally expanded effectors, and if this is patient tissue, pull the PD-L1 IHC and Tumor Mutational Burden — the biology says this sample should respond to checkpoint blockade, and that's a testable, near-term prediction.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;5;135m\u001b[1m  ━━ Continue your analysis ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\r\n"]
